cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR. 

The paper presents a framework for learning object structures from web images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The framework involves active learning and question-answering, which are also common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The discriminative loss used in the framework measures the fitness to human answers, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
